---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Ported from the app's canonical policy at app.houndstack.com/legal/sms
// (the public SMS program disclosure used for Twilio toll-free verification
// and TCPA compliance) so the two never disagree; update both together.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SMS Consent &amp; Messaging Policy | HoundStack"
  description="How HoundStack collects consent for text messages, what we send, and how to opt out."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container-narrow prose">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1>SMS Consent &amp; Messaging Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: July 14, 2026</p>

      <h2>The short version</h2>
      <p>
        HoundStack only sends text messages to people who ask for them, and every message we send
        includes a way to stop. Reply <strong>STOP</strong> to any message to opt out immediately,
        or <strong>HELP</strong> for assistance.
      </p>

      <h2>What messages we send</h2>
      <p>HoundStack sends two kinds of text messages, and both require prior consent:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Account messages to business users.</strong> If you create a HoundStack account
          and provide a mobile number with consent, we may text you login codes and important
          account or service notifications.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Service messages to a business's customers.</strong> Pet-care businesses that
          run on HoundStack can text their own customers things like visit reminders,
          "your technician is on the way" notices, visit-completed confirmations, portal sign-in
          codes, overdue-invoice reminders, and review requests. These messages are sent only to
          customers who gave that business their number and consent to be contacted.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not send marketing or promotional cold texts, and we never text numbers that have
        not opted in.
      </p>

      <h2>How consent is collected</h2>
      <p>
        Business users opt in during account creation by entering a mobile number and checking an
        unticked-by-default consent box with this language:
      </p>
      <blockquote>
        "I agree to receive text messages from HoundStack at the number provided, including login
        codes and service notifications. Message frequency varies. Message &amp; data rates may
        apply. Reply STOP to opt out or HELP for help. Consent is not a condition of purchase."
      </blockquote>
      <p>
        We record when consent was given, the number it covers, and the exact language shown.
        Businesses using HoundStack to message their customers are responsible for collecting
        equivalent consent from those customers, and the platform enforces opt-outs for them
        automatically.
      </p>

      <h2>Message frequency and rates</h2>
      <p>
        Message frequency varies based on your account activity and service schedule. Message and
        data rates may apply according to your mobile carrier's plan. Consent to receive texts is
        never a condition of purchasing any product or service.
      </p>

      <h2 id="opt-out">How to opt out (SMS un-consent)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Reply STOP</strong> to any message you receive from HoundStack or from a
          business using HoundStack. Opt-outs take effect immediately and are enforced
          automatically: the platform blocks further texts to your number.
        </li>
        <li>
          Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message for assistance.
        </li>
        <li>
          Business users can also remove their mobile number or withdraw texting consent in
          Settings, and customers of a HoundStack business can manage notification preferences in
          their client portal or by contacting the business directly.
        </li>
        <li>
          You can always email <a href="mailto:support@houndstack.com">support@houndstack.com</a>
          and we will process the opt-out for you.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Privacy of your mobile information</h2>
      <p>
        No mobile information will be shared with third parties or affiliates for marketing or
        promotional purposes. Text messaging originator opt-in data and consent are not shared
        with any third parties, except with our SMS delivery provider solely to send the messages
        you asked for. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for full details.
      </p>

      <h2>Carriers</h2>
      <p>
        Messages are delivered over the networks of participating carriers. Carriers are not
        liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy:
        <a href="mailto:support@houndstack.com">support@houndstack.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding-top: clamp(40px, 6vw, 72px);
    padding-bottom: clamp(48px, 7vw, 88px);
  }

  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>
